rformance profiles.\n\n<h2>Pros and Cons of Khan Academy SAT Math Prep<\/h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Pros:<\/strong>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Free access to high-quality, official SAT math practice materials<\/li>\n    <li>Adaptive learning system personalizes study plans<\/li>\n    <li>Comprehensive coverage of SAT math topics aligned with the exam<\/li>\n    <li>Detailed, step-by-step explanations improve conceptual understanding<\/li>\n    <li>Convenient online platform accessible anytime<\/li>\n  <\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><strong>Cons:<\/strong>\n  <ul>\n    <li>Lacks live tutoring or personalized instructor interaction<\/li>\n    <li>Limited focus on test-taking strategies and time management<\/li>\n    <li>Some students may find the self-paced format less motivating<\/li>\n  <\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<h2>The Impact of Khan Academy on SAT Math Preparation<\/h2>\n\nSince the partnership announcement with the College Board in 2015, Khan Academy SAT math prep has reshaped the test prep landscape. Its free availability has contributed to leveling the playing field, offering students regardless of socioeconomic status the chance to prepare effectively. Studies have shown that students who use Khan Academy’s SAT prep tools tend to improve their scores, although the degree of improvement varies based on engagement and study habits.\n\nDespite some limitations, Khan Academy’s model exemplifies how technology and strategic partnerships can enhance educational equity. For many students, it serves as a solid foundation for SAT math preparation, especially when supplemented with other resources such as practice with test-taking strategies or occasional tutoring sessions.\n\nIn summary, Khan Academy SAT math prep provides a well-rounded, accessible, and data-driven approach to mastering the math section of the SAT. Its adaptive learning, official content alignment, and cost-free model make it an attractive option for students seeking to improve their scores with minimal financial investment